question_title: What will be the value of "Market Yield on U.S. Treasury Securities at 2-Year Constant Maturity, Quoted on an Investment Basis" on 2026-02-12?
summary: The 2-year Treasury yield (DGS2) is currently at 3.57% with very low recent volatility. Fed policy is on hold at 3.50-3.75%, providing a strong anchor. The main uncertainty is the CPI release on February 11 (one day before resolution), which could move yields 10-15 bps in either direction depending on whether inflation surprises hot or cool. The 5-trading-day horizon limits drift potential. Distribution is centered on current value with moderate tails for event risk.

factors.description: Current yield anchoring: 2-year yield at 3.57% closely tracks Fed funds (3.50-3.75%), providing strong anchor for short-horizon forecast
Low recent volatility: Daily std ~2.5 bps over past 6 weeks, range only 16 bps (3.45-3.61%), suggesting stable near-term distribution
CPI release Feb 11: Major event one day before resolution could move yields 10-15 bps in either direction - adds symmetric tail risk
Fed on hold: No FOMC meeting before Feb 12, Fed policy unchanged since Jan, reduces policy-driven volatility
Inflation concerns still present: Recent Fed guidance suggests rates could rise if inflation persists, slight upside tail risk
